Date Published:2019-12-04 00:00:00      
For dealers the price has been reduced to Tk14 from Tk23 per kg The government has reduced the price of Diammonium Phosphate (DAP) fertilizer to Tk16 per kg from Tk25 for farmers.  For dealers the price has been reduced to Tk14 from Tk23 per kg, said Agriculture Minister Mohammad Abdur Razzaque said.  The minister came up with the information while talking at a press briefing at the secretariat on Wednesday, reports UNB. The new price will be become effective very soon, he said.
